Implement Phase 47: Real /team Team Workspace.

Goal:
Replace the current mostly static Team Roster page with a real DB-backed team workspace for zDash.

Current state:
- frontend/src/pages/TeamRoster.tsx renders canonical AI agents from CANONICAL_AGENTS.
- It uses useAgents() only for live agent health.
- It has a hardcoded message panel from ceo -> janie.
- It is not a real organization/team/member management page.

Target:
Build a real /team page that manages organization users, roles, invitations, workspace access, AI agent assignments, activity, and audit-safe actions.

Hard requirements:
- No secrets printed.
- No .env files tracked.
- All backend responses must use zDash API envelope: { ok, data, error, timestamp }.
- No frontend runtime crash on undefined/null arrays.
- No live destructive actions without confirmation.
- Must remain safe in development and production.
- Do not break existing TeamRoster tests; update them to match the real page.
- Preserve existing AI agent roster as a tab/section, not as the entire /team page.

Backend tasks:

1. Create or finalize team domain models
Add DB-backed models if missing:
- TeamMember
  - id
  - organization_id
  - workspace_id nullable
  - user_id nullable
  - email
  - display_name
  - role: owner | admin | operator | analyst | developer | viewer
  - status: active | invited | suspended | removed
  - avatar_url nullable
  - last_seen_at nullable
  - created_at / updated_at
- TeamInvitation
  - id
  - organization_id
  - workspace_id nullable
  - email
  - role
  - token_hash
  - status: pending | accepted | revoked | expired
  - invited_by
  - expires_at
  - created_at / updated_at
- TeamWorkspaceAccess
  - id
  - organization_id
  - workspace_id
  - member_id
  - access_level: owner | manage | write | read
  - created_at / updated_at
- TeamAgentAssignment
  - id
  - organization_id
  - workspace_id
  - member_id nullable
  - agent_id
  - assignment_role: owner | reviewer | runner | observer
  - created_at / updated_at

Use existing Base/session/migration style in repo.

2. Repository/service layer
Create:
- backend/app/team/models.py
- backend/app/team/repositories.py
- backend/app/team/service.py
- backend/app/team/schemas.py

Service functions:
- list_members(org_id, workspace_id optional)
- get_member(org_id, member_id)
- invite_member(org_id, workspace_id, email, role, invited_by)
- resend_invitation(org_id, invitation_id, actor)
- revoke_invitation(org_id, invitation_id, actor)
- update_member_role(org_id, member_id, role, actor)
- suspend_member(org_id, member_id, actor)
- reactivate_member(org_id, member_id, actor)
- remove_member(org_id, member_id, actor)
- list_invitations(org_id, workspace_id optional)
- list_workspace_access(org_id, workspace_id)
- grant_workspace_access(org_id, workspace_id, member_id, access_level, actor)
- revoke_workspace_access(org_id, access_id, actor)
- list_agent_assignments(org_id, workspace_id optional)
- assign_agent(org_id, workspace_id, agent_id, member_id, assignment_role, actor)
- unassign_agent(org_id, assignment_id, actor)
- get_team_activity(org_id, workspace_id optional, limit)

Rules:
- Validate email.
- Validate role.
- Owner cannot remove/suspend self.
- Last owner cannot be removed or downgraded.
- Invitations must be token-hashed; never return raw token except immediately at creation in development-safe form if necessary.
- Redact secrets in audit logs.
- All mutations emit audit/event entries.

3. API
Create:
- backend/app/api/team.py

Routes:
- GET /api/team/members
- GET /api/team/members/{member_id}
- POST /api/team/invitations
- GET /api/team/invitations
- POST /api/team/invitations/{invitation_id}/resend
- POST /api/team/invitations/{invitation_id}/revoke
- PATCH /api/team/members/{member_id}/role
- POST /api/team/members/{member_id}/suspend
- POST /api/team/members/{member_id}/reactivate
- DELETE /api/team/members/{member_id}
- GET /api/team/workspace-access
- POST /api/team/workspace-access
- DELETE /api/team/workspace-access/{access_id}
- GET /api/team/agent-assignments
- POST /api/team/agent-assignments
- DELETE /api/team/agent-assignments/{assignment_id}
- GET /api/team/activity
- GET /api/team/summary

Every endpoint returns zDash envelope.
Use RBAC permissions if existing ones exist. If missing, add safe permission mapping:
- team_read
- team_manage
- team_invite
- team_remove
- team_assign_agents

If RBAC enum cannot be safely extended, reuse closest admin/team permissions and document.

4. Seed/default dev data
When no members exist for an org, return or seed:
- current authenticated user as owner/admin
- optional system operator member
- no secrets
- development-only generated invitations must be clearly mock/dev

