Update frontend/src/api/types.ts and frontend/src/api/endpoints.ts with:
- TeamMember
- TeamInvitation
- TeamWorkspaceAccess
- TeamAgentAssignment
- TeamActivity
- TeamSummary
- listTeamMembers()
- listTeamInvitations()
- inviteTeamMember()
- revokeTeamInvitation()
- resendTeamInvitation()
- updateTeamMemberRole()
- suspendTeamMember()
- reactivateTeamMember()
- removeTeamMember()
- listTeamWorkspaceAccess()
- grantTeamWorkspaceAccess()
- revokeTeamWorkspaceAccess()
- listTeamAgentAssignments()
- assignTeamAgent()
- unassignTeamAgent()
- getTeamActivity()
- getTeamSummary()

Fallback mocks must be complete, deterministic, safe, and never require live backend for tests.

6. Frontend hook
Create:
- frontend/src/hooks/useTeam.ts

Hook state:
- members
- invitations
- workspaceAccess
- agentAssignments
- activity
- summary
- loading
- error
- mutation loading states

Hook actions:
- inviteMember
- updateRole
- suspendMember
- reactivateMember
- removeMember
- resendInvite
- revokeInvite
- grantAccess
- revokeAccess
- assignAgent
- unassignAgent
- refetch

All actions catch API errors and set a visible error without crashing.

7. Real /team UI
Replace frontend/src/pages/TeamRoster.tsx with a real team workspace page.

Sections/tabs:
- Overview
  - total members
  - active members
  - pending invitations
  - admins/operators/viewers counts
  - safety warning for last owner
- Members
  - searchable/filterable member table
  - role badge
  - status badge
  - last seen
  - actions: change role, suspend/reactivate, remove
  - confirmations for suspend/remove
- Invitations
  - invite member form
  - email input with id/name/autocomplete
  - role select with id/name
  - workspace select if available
  - pending invites table
  - resend/revoke actions
- Workspace Access
  - workspace access table
  - grant/revoke access
- Agent Assignments
  - preserve current canonical AI agents roster here
  - show live agent status from useAgents()
  - assign human owner/reviewer/runner/observer to agent
- Activity
  - audit/event timeline of team changes

Defensive rendering:
- Every array must be guarded with Array.isArray.
- No .map/.length on undefined.
- No .toLowerCase on undefined.
- All form fields must have id or name.
- All action buttons handle rejected promises.

8. Preserve current AI team value
Move the current static canonical agent roster into a component:
- frontend/src/components/team/AgentAssignmentBoard.tsx

It should keep:
- canonical agent cards
- live status from useAgents
- pagination
- existing message panel may become "Agent Message Panel"
But it should not be the only /team content.

9. Tests
Add/update:
- frontend/src/tests/TeamRoster.test.tsx
- frontend/src/tests/TeamActions.test.tsx
- frontend/src/tests/ApiMockHarness.test.ts
- backend/app/tests/test_team_api.py
- backend/app/tests/test_team_service.py

Frontend tests:
- /team renders Team Workspace heading
- renders overview cards
- renders members table
- invite form has id/name fields
- clicking invite calls API mock and shows pending invitation
- suspend/remove actions require confirmation or safe flow
- agent assignment board renders canonical agents
- no live /api calls
- no act warnings

Backend tests:
- list members returns envelope
- invite member returns envelope
- invalid role returns envelope error
- cannot remove last owner
- suspend/reactivate works
- agent assignment dry/safe semantics
- all HTTP exceptions remain enveloped

10. Docs
Create:
- docs/runbooks/REAL_TEAM_WORKSPACE.md
- docs/reports/PHASE47_REAL_TEAM_WORKSPACE_REPORT.md

Docs must cover:
- team architecture
- role model
- invitation flow
- workspace access model
- agent assignment model
- audit/safety model
- local development behavior

Validation:
- cd backend && python -m ruff format --check app tests
- cd backend && python -m ruff check app tests
- cd backend && pytest app/tests/test_team_api.py app/tests/test_team_service.py
- cd frontend && npm test -- src/tests/TeamRoster.test.tsx
- cd frontend && npm test -- src/tests/TeamActions.test.tsx
- cd frontend && npm run build
- make validate-fast

Acceptance criteria:
- /team loads without ErrorBoundary crash.
- /team is real team management, not only static AI roster.
- Team members and invitations are DB-backed or repository-backed with deterministic dev seed.
- All API responses are zDash envelopes.
- Mutations show clear UI errors and do not crash.
- Agent roster is preserved under Agent Assignments.
- All tests pass.
- make validate-fast passes.
- No secrets.
- No .env tracked.
